(117, 1, '2018-10-11 17:51:08', '2018-10-11 14:51:08', 'pecify a single box-shadow using:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Two, three, or four <code><a href=\"http://docset.velocity/CSS.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length.html\">&lt;length&gt;</a></code> values.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>If only two values are given, they are interpreted as <code><a href=\"http://docset.velocity/CSS.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-shadow.html?v=a#&lt;offset-x&gt; &lt;offset-y&gt;\">&lt;offset-x&gt;&lt;offset-y&gt;</a></code> values.</li>\r\n 	<li>If a third value is given, it is interpreted as a <code><a href=\"http://docset.velocity/CSS.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-shadow.html?v=a#&lt;blur-radius&gt;\">&lt;blur-radius&gt;</a></code>.</li>\r\n 	<li>If a fourth value is given, it is interpreted as a <code><a href=\"http://docset.velocity/CSS.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-shadow.html?v=a#&lt;spread-radius&gt;\">&lt;spread-radius&gt;</a></code>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Optionally, the <code><a href=\"http://docset.velocity/CSS.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-shadow.html?v=a#inset\">inset</a></code> keyword.</li>\r\n 	<li>Optionally, a <code><a href=\"http://docset.velocity/CSS.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/box-shadow.html?v=a#&lt;color&gt;\">&lt;color&gt;</a></code> value.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'box-shadow syntax', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '114-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-11 17:51:08', '2018-10-11 14:51:08', '', 114, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2018/10/11/114-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(118, 1, '2018-10-11 17:52:15', '2018-10-11 14:52:15', '<code>inset</code>If not specified (default), the shadow is assumed to be a drop shadow (as if the box were raised above the content).\r\nThe presence of the <code>inset</code> keyword changes the shadow to one inside the frame (as if the content was depressed inside the box). Inset shadows are drawn inside the border (even transparent ones), above the background, but below content.<a id=\"&lt;offset-x&gt; &lt;offset-y&gt;\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: inherit; text-decoration: none;\" name=\"&lt;offset-x&gt; &lt;offset-y&gt;\"></a><code>&lt;offset-x&gt;</code> <code>&lt;offset-y&gt;</code>These are two <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The &lt;length&gt; CSS data type represents a distance value. Lengths can be used in numerous CSS properties, such as width, height, margin, padding, border-width, font-size, and text-shadow.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> values to set the shadow offset. <code>&lt;offset-x&gt;</code> specifies the horizontal distance. Negative values place the shadow to the left of the element. <code>&lt;offset-y&gt;</code> specifies the vertical distance. Negative values place the shadow above the element. See <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The &lt;length&gt; CSS data type represents a distance value. Lengths can be used in numerous CSS properties, such as width, height, margin, padding, border-width, font-size, and text-shadow.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> for possible units.\r\nIf both values are <code>0</code>, the shadow is placed behind the element (and may generate a blur effect if <code>&lt;blur-radius&gt;</code> and/or <code>&lt;spread-radius&gt;</code> is set).<a id=\"&lt;blur-radius&gt;\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: inherit; text-decoration: none;\" name=\"&lt;blur-radius&gt;\"></a><code>&lt;blur-radius&gt;</code>This is a third <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The &lt;length&gt; CSS data type represents a distance value. Lengths can be used in numerous CSS properties, such as width, height, margin, padding, border-width, font-size, and text-shadow.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> value. The larger this value, the bigger the blur, so the shadow becomes bigger and lighter. Negative values are not allowed. If not specified, it will be <code>0</code> (the shadow\'s edge is sharp). The specification does not include an exact algorithm for how the blur radius should be calculated, however, it does elaborate as follows:', 'box-shadow values', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'box-shadow-values', '', '', '2018-10-11 17:55:28', '2018-10-11 14:55:28', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=118', 0, 'post', '', 16),
