(139, 1, '2018-10-15 18:53:39', '2018-10-15 15:53:39', 'The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> element</strong> represents the root (top-level element) of an HTML document, so it is also referred to as the <em>root element</em>. All other elements must be descendants of this element.\r\n\r\nelement in a document.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/body.html\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: rgb(56, 120, 148); text-decoration: none;\"&gt;<code>&lt;body&gt;</code> element either that is not empty or whose start tag is present.Permitted parentsAs the root element of a document, or wherever a subdocument fragment is allowed in a compound document.Permitted ARIA rolesNoneDOM interface<a title=\"The HTMLHtmlElement interface serves as the root node for a given HTML document.  This object inherits the properties and methods described in the HTMLElement interface.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLHtmlElement.html\"><code>HTMLHtmlElement</code></a>\r\n<h2 id=\"Attributes\" class=\"highlight-spanned\"><span class=\"highlight-span\">Attributes</span></h2>\r\nThis element includes the <a href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes.html\">global attributes</a>.\r\n<dl>\r\n 	<dt><a name=\"attr-manifest\"></a><code>manifest</code> <i class=\"icon-trash\"></i></dt>\r\n 	<dd>Specifies the URI of a resource manifest indicating resources that should be cached locally. See <a href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Using_the_application_cache.html\">Using the application cache</a> for details.</dd>\r\n 	<dt><a name=\"attr-version\"></a><code>version</code> <i class=\"icon-trash\"></i></dt>\r\n 	<dd>Specifies the version of the HTML <a class=\"glossaryLink\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-image: initial; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; cursor: help; border-color: initial initial #aaaaaa initial; border-style: initial initial dashed initial;\" title=\"Document Type Definition: &lt;!DOCTYPE&gt; informs the browser which version of HTML (or XML) you used to write the document. Doctype is a declaration, not a tag; you can also refer to it as &quot;document type declaration&quot;, or &quot;DTD&quot; for short.\" href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/DTD\">Document Type Definition</a> that governs the current document. This attribute is not needed, because it is redundant with the version information in the document type declaration.</dd>\r\n 	<dt><a name=\"attr-xmlns\"></a><code>xmlns</code></dt>\r\n 	<dd>Specifies the XML Namespace of the document. Default value is <code>\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"</code>. This is required in documents parsed with XML parsers, and optional in text/html documents.</dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n<h2 id=\"Example\" class=\"highlight-spanned\"><span class=\"highlight-span\">Example</span></h2>\r\n<pre class=\"brush: html line-numbers  language-html\"><code class=\" language-html\"><span class=\"token doctype\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span>\r\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>html<span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\r\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>head<span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>...<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>head<span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\r\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>body<span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>...<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>body<span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\r\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>html<span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span></code></pre>', '<html>', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '135-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-15 18:53:39', '2018-10-15 15:53:39', '', 135, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2018/10/15/135-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(140, 1, '2018-10-15 18:55:28', '2018-10-15 15:55:28', 'Metadata contains information about the page. This includes information about styles, scripts and data to help software (<a class=\"glossaryLink\" title=\"search engines: A search engine is a software system that collects information from the World Wide Web and presents it to users who are looking for specific information.\" href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/search_engine\">search engines</a>, <a class=\"glossaryLink\" title=\"browsers: A Web browser is a program that retrieves and displays pages from the Web, and lets users access further pages through hyperlinks.\" href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Browser\">browsers</a>, etc.) use and render the page. Metadata for styles and scripts may be defined in the page or link to another file that has the information.\r\n<table class=\"standard-table\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Element</th>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;link&gt; element specifies relationships between the current document and an external resource. Possible uses for this element include defining a relational framework for navigation. This element is most used to link to style sheets.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/link.html\"><code>&lt;link&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> element</strong> specifies relationships between the current document and an external resource. Possible uses for this element include defining a relational framework for navigation. This element is most used to link to <a title=\"Cascading Style Sheets\" href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/CSS\">style sheets</a>.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;meta&gt; element represents metadata that cannot be represented by other HTML meta-related elements, like &lt;base&gt;, &lt;link&gt;, &lt;script&gt;, &lt;style&gt; or &lt;title&gt;.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/meta.html\"><code>&lt;meta&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;meta&gt;</code> element</strong> represents <a class=\"glossaryLink\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-image: initial; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; cursor: help; border-color: initial initial #aaaaaa initial; border-style: initial initial dashed initial;\" title=\"metadata: Metadata is — in its very simplest definition — data that describes data. For example, an HTML document is data, but HTML can also contain metadata in its &lt;head&gt; element that describes the document — for example who wrote it, and its summary.\" href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Metadata\">metadata</a> that cannot be represented by other HTML meta-related elements, like <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;base&gt; element specifies the base URL to use for all relative URLs contained within a document. There can be only one &lt;base&gt; element in a document.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/base.html\"><code>&lt;base&gt;</code></a>, <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;link&gt; element specifies relationships between the current document and an external resource. Possible uses for this element include defining a relational framework for navigation. This element is most used to link to style sheets.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/link.html\"><code>&lt;link&gt;</code></a>, <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;script&gt; element is used to embed or reference an executable script.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/script.html\"><code>&lt;script&gt;</code></a>, <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;style&gt; element contains style information for a document, or part of a document. By default, the style instructions written inside that element are expected to be CSS.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/style.html\"><code>&lt;style&gt;</code></a> or <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;title&gt; element defines the title of the document, shown in a browser\'s title bar or on the page\'s tab. It can only contain text, and any contained tags are ignored.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/title.html\"><code>&lt;title&gt;</code></a>.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;style&gt; element contains style information for a document, or part of a document. By default, the style instructions written inside that element are expected to be CSS.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/style.html\"><code>&lt;style&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> element</strong> contains style information for a document, or part of a document. By default, the style instructions written inside that element are expected to be <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS\">CSS</a>.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Document metadata', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'document-metadata', '', '', '2018-10-15 18:55:28', '2018-10-15 15:55:28', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=140', 0, 'post', '', 1),
