(158, 1, '2018-10-15 18:59:05', '2018-10-15 15:59:05', 'Use the HTML inline text semantic to define the meaning, structure, or style of a word, line, or any arbitrary piece of text.\r\n<table class=\"standard-table\" style=\"height: 1943px;\" width=\"819\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Element</th>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;a&gt; element (or anchor element) creates a hyperlink to other web pages, files, locations within the same page, email addresses, or any other URL.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/a.html\"><code>&lt;a&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element</strong> (or <em>anchor</em> element) creates a hyperlink to other web pages, files, locations within the same page, email addresses, or any other URL.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;abbr&gt; element represents an abbreviation and optionally provides a full description for it. If present, the title attribute must contain this full description and nothing else.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/abbr.html\"><code>&lt;abbr&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;abbr&gt;</code> element</strong> represents an abbreviation and optionally provides a full description for it. If present, the <code><a href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes.html#attr-title\">title</a></code> attribute must contain this full description and nothing else.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;b&gt; element represents a span of text stylistically different from normal text, without conveying any special importance or relevance, and that is typically rendered in boldface.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/b.html\"><code>&lt;b&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;b&gt;</code> element</strong> represents a span of text stylistically different from normal text, without conveying any special importance or relevance, and that is typically rendered in boldface.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;bdi&gt; element (bidirectional isolation) isolates a span of text that might be formatted in a different direction from other text outside it.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/bdi.html\"><code>&lt;bdi&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;bdi&gt;</code> element</strong> (<em>bidirectional isolation</em>) isolates a span of text that might be formatted in a different direction from other text outside it.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;bdo&gt; element (bidirectional override) is used to override the current directionality of text. It causes the directionality of the characters to be ignored in favor of the specified directionality.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/bdo.html\"><code>&lt;bdo&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;bdo&gt;</code> element</strong> (<em>bidirectional override</em>) is used to override the current directionality of text. It causes the directionality of the characters to be ignored in favor of the specified directionality.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;br&gt; element produces a line break in text (carriage-return). It is useful for writing a poem or an address, where the division of lines is significant.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/br.html\"><code>&lt;br&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;br&gt;</code> element</strong> produces a line break in text (carriage-return). It is useful for writing a poem or an address, where the division of lines is significant.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;cite&gt; element represents a reference to a creative work. It must include the title of a work or a URL reference, which may be in an abbreviated form according to the conventions used for the addition of citation metadata.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/cite.html\"><code>&lt;cite&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML &lt;cite&gt; element</strong> represents a reference to a creative work. It must include the title of a work or a URL reference, which may be in an abbreviated form according to the conventions used for the addition of citation metadata.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;code&gt; element represents a fragment of computer code. By default, it is displayed in the browser\'s default monospace font.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/code.html\"><code>&lt;code&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> element</strong> represents a fragment of computer code. By default, it is displayed in the browser\'s default monospace font.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;data&gt; element links a given content with a machine-readable translation. If the content is time- or date-related, the &lt;time&gt; element must be used.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/data.html\"><code>&lt;data&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;data&gt;</code> element</strong> links a given content with a machine-readable translation. If the content is time- or date-related, the <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;time&gt; element represents either a time on a 24-hour clock or a precise date in the Gregorian calendar (with optional time and timezone information).\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/time.html\"><code>&lt;time&gt;</code></a> element must be used.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;dfn&gt; element represents the defining instance of a term.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dfn.html\"><code>&lt;dfn&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML &lt;dfn&gt; element</strong> represents the defining instance of a term.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;em&gt; element marks text that has stress emphasis. The &lt;em&gt; element can be nested, with each level of nesting indicating a greater degree of emphasis.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/em.html\"><code>&lt;em&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> element</strong> marks text that has stress emphasis. The <code>&lt;em&gt;</code> element can be nested, with each level of nesting indicating a greater degree of emphasis.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;i&gt; element represents a range of text that is set off from the normal text for some reason, for example, technical terms, foreign language phrases, or fictional character thoughts. It is typically displayed in italic type.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/i.html\"><code>&lt;i&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;i&gt;</code> element</strong> represents a range of text that is set off from the normal text for some reason, for example, technical terms, foreign language phrases, or fictional character thoughts. It is typically displayed in italic type.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;kbd&gt; element represents user input and produces an inline element displayed in the browser\'s default monospace font.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/kbd.html\"><code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code> element</strong> represents user input and produces an inline element displayed in the browser\'s default monospace font.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;mark&gt; element represents highlighted text, i.e., a run of text marked for reference purpose, due to its relevance in a particular context.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/mark.html\"><code>&lt;mark&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;mark&gt;</code> element</strong> represents highlighted text, i.e., a run of text marked for reference purpose, due to its <em>relevance</em> in a particular context.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;q&gt; element  indicates that the enclosed text is a short inline quotation. This element is intended for short quotations that don\'t require paragraph breaks; for long quotations use the &lt;blockquote&gt; element.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/q.html\"><code>&lt;q&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;q&gt;</code> element </strong>indicates that the enclosed text is a short inline quotation. This element is intended for short quotations that don\'t require paragraph breaks; for long quotations use the <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;blockquote&gt; Element (or HTML Block Quotation Element) indicates that the enclosed text is an extended quotation. Usually, this is rendered visually by indentation (see Notes for how to change it). A URL for the source of the quotation may be given using the cite attribute, while a text representation of the source can be given using the &lt;cite&gt; element.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/blockquote.html\"><code>&lt;blockquote&gt;</code></a> element.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;rp&gt; element is used to provide fall-back parentheses for browsers that do not support display of ruby annotations using the &lt;ruby&gt; element.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/rp.html\"><code>&lt;rp&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;rp&gt;</code> element</strong> is used to provide fall-back parentheses for browsers that do not support display of ruby annotations using the <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;ruby&gt; element represents a ruby annotation. Ruby annotations are for showing pronunciation of East Asian characters.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ruby.html\"><code>&lt;ruby&gt;</code></a> element.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;rt&gt; element embraces pronunciation of characters presented in a ruby annotations, which are used to describe the pronunciation of East Asian characters. This element is always used inside a &lt;ruby&gt; element.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/rt.html\"><code>&lt;rt&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;rt&gt;</code> element</strong> embraces pronunciation of characters presented in a ruby annotations, which are used to describe the pronunciation of East Asian characters. This element is always used inside a <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;ruby&gt; element represents a ruby annotation. Ruby annotations are for showing pronunciation of East Asian characters.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ruby.html\"><code>&lt;ruby&gt;</code></a> element.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;rtc&gt; element embraces semantic annotations of characters presented in a ruby of &lt;rb&gt; elements used inside of &lt;ruby&gt; element. &lt;rb&gt; elements can have both pronunciation (&lt;rt&gt;) and semantic (&lt;rtc&gt;) annotations.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/rtc.html\"><code>&lt;rtc&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;rtc&gt;</code> element</strong> embraces semantic annotations of characters presented in a ruby of <a class=\"new\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/rb.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>&lt;rb&gt;</code></a> elements used inside of <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;ruby&gt; element represents a ruby annotation. Ruby annotations are for showing pronunciation of East Asian characters.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ruby.html\"><code>&lt;ruby&gt;</code></a> element. <a class=\"new\" title=\"The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/rb.html\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>&lt;rb&gt;</code></a>elements can have both pronunciation (<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;rt&gt; element embraces pronunciation of characters presented in a ruby annotations, which are used to describe the pronunciation of East Asian characters. This element is always used inside a &lt;ruby&gt; element.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/rt.html\"><code>&lt;rt&gt;</code></a>) and semantic (<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;rtc&gt; element embraces semantic annotations of characters presented in a ruby of &lt;rb&gt; elements used inside of &lt;ruby&gt; element. &lt;rb&gt; elements can have both pronunciation (&lt;rt&gt;) and semantic (&lt;rtc&gt;) annotations.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/rtc.html\"><code>&lt;rtc&gt;</code></a>) annotations.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;ruby&gt; element represents a ruby annotation. Ruby annotations are for showing pronunciation of East Asian characters.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ruby.html\"><code>&lt;ruby&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;ruby&gt;</code> element</strong> represents a ruby annotation. Ruby annotations are for showing pronunciation of East Asian characters.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;s&gt; element renders text with a strikethrough, or a line through it. Use the &lt;s&gt; element to represent things that are no longer relevant or no longer accurate. However, &lt;s&gt; is not appropriate when indicating document edits; for that, use the &lt;del&gt; and &lt;ins&gt; elements, as appropriate.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/s.html\"><code>&lt;s&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;s&gt;</code> element</strong> renders text with a strikethrough, or a line through it. Use the <code>&lt;s&gt;</code> element to represent things that are no longer relevant or no longer accurate. However, <code>&lt;s&gt;</code> is not appropriate when indicating document edits; for that, use the <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;del&gt; element represents a range of text that has been deleted from a document. This element is often (but need not be) rendered with strike-through text.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/del.html\"><code>&lt;del&gt;</code></a> and <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;ins&gt; element represents a range of text that has been added to a document.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ins.html\"><code>&lt;ins&gt;</code></a> elements, as appropriate.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;samp&gt; element is an element intended to identify sample output from a computer program. It is usually displayed in the browser\'s default monotype font (such as Lucida Console).\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/samp.html\"><code>&lt;samp&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;samp&gt;</code> element</strong> is an element intended to identify sample output from a computer program. It is usually displayed in the browser\'s default monotype font (such as Lucida Console).</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;small&gt; element makes the text font size one size smaller (for example, from large to medium, or from small to x-small) down to the browser\'s minimum font size.  In HTML5, this element is repurposed to represent side-comments and small print, including copyright and legal text, independent of its styled presentation.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/small.html\"><code>&lt;small&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;small&gt;</code></strong> <strong>element </strong>makes the text <em>font size</em> one size smaller (for example, from large to medium, or from small to x-small) down to the browser\'s minimum font size.  In HTML5, this element is repurposed to represent side-comments and small print, including copyright and legal text, independent of its styled presentation.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;span&gt; element is a generic inline container for phrasing content, which does not inherently represent anything. It can be used to group elements for styling purposes (using the class or id attributes), or because they share attribute values, such as lang.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/span.html\"><code>&lt;span&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> element</strong> is a generic inline container for phrasing content, which does not inherently represent anything. It can be used to group elements for styling purposes (using the <code>class</code> or <code>id</code> attributes), or because they share attribute values, such as <code>lang</code>.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;strong&gt; element gives text strong importance, and is typically displayed in bold.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/strong.html\"><code>&lt;strong&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML </strong><code><strong>&lt;strong&gt;</strong></code><strong> element</strong> gives text strong importance, and is typically displayed in bold.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;sub&gt; element defines a span of text that should be displayed, for typographic reasons, lower, and often smaller, than the main span of text.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/sub.html\"><code>&lt;sub&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;sub&gt;</code> element</strong> defines a span of text that should be displayed, for typographic reasons, lower, and often smaller, than the main span of text.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;sup&gt; element defines a span of text that should be displayed, for typographic reasons, higher, and often smaller, than the main span of text.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/sup.html\"><code>&lt;sup&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;sup&gt;</code> element</strong> defines a span of text that should be displayed, for typographic reasons, higher, and often smaller, than the main span of text.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;time&gt; element represents either a time on a 24-hour clock or a precise date in the Gregorian calendar (with optional time and timezone information).\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/time.html\"><code>&lt;time&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;time&gt;</code> element</strong> represents either a time on a 24-hour clock or a precise date in the <a class=\"external external-icon\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gregorian_calendar\">Gregorian calendar</a> (with optional time and timezone information).</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;u&gt; element renders text with an underline, a line under the baseline of its content. In HTML5, this element represents a span of text with an unarticulated, though explicitly rendered, non-textual annotation, such as labeling the text as being a proper name in Chinese text (a Chinese proper name mark), or labeling the text as being misspelled.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/u.html\"><code>&lt;u&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;u&gt;</code> element</strong> renders text with an underline, a line under the baseline of its content. In HTML5, this element represents a span of text with an unarticulated, though explicitly rendered, non-textual annotation, such as labeling the text as being a proper name in Chinese text (a Chinese proper name mark), or labeling the text as being misspelled.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;var&gt; element represents a variable in a mathematical expression or a programming context.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/var.html\"><code>&lt;var&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;var&gt;</code> element</strong> represents a variable in a mathematical expression or a programming context.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;wbr&gt; element represents a word break opportunity—a position within text where the browser may optionally break a line, though its line-breaking rules would not otherwise create a break at that location.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/wbr.html\"><code>&lt;wbr&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;wbr&gt;</code> element</strong> represents a word break opportunity—a position within text where the browser may optionally break a line, though its line-breaking rules would not otherwise create a break at that location.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Inline text semantics', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '155-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-15 18:59:05', '2018-10-15 15:59:05', '', 155, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2018/10/15/155-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(159, 1, '2018-10-16 13:35:22', '2018-10-16 10:35:22', 'HTML supports various multimedia resources such as images, audio, and video.\r\n<table class=\"standard-table\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Element</th>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;area&gt; element defines a hot-spot region on an image, and optionally associates it with a hypertext link. This element is used only within a &lt;map&gt; element.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/area.html\"><code>&lt;area&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;area&gt;</code> element</strong> defines a hot-spot region on an image, and optionally associates it with a <a class=\"glossaryLink\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-image: initial; color: inherit; text-decoration: none; cursor: help; border-color: initial initial #aaaaaa initial; border-style: initial initial dashed initial;\" title=\"hypertext link: Hyperlinks connect webpages or data items to one another. In HTML, &lt;a&gt; elements define hyperlinks from a spot on a webpage (like a text string or image) to another spot on some other webpage (or even on the same page).\" href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Hyperlink\">hypertext link</a>. This element is used only within a <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;map&gt; element is used with &lt;area&gt; elements to define an image map (a clickable link area).\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/map.html\"><code>&lt;map&gt;</code></a> element.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;audio&gt; element is used to embed sound content in documents. It may contain one or more audio sources, represented using the src attribute or the &lt;source&gt; element: the browser will choose the most suitable one. It can also be the destination for streamed media, using a MediaStream.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/audio.html\"><code>&lt;audio&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;audio&gt;</code> element</strong> is used to embed sound content in documents. It may contain one or more audio sources, represented using the <code>src</code> attribute or the <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;source&gt; element specifies multiple media resources for either the &lt;picture&gt;, the &lt;audio&gt; or the &lt;video&gt; element. It is an empty element. It is commonly used to serve the same media content in multiple formats supported by different browsers.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/source.html\"><code>&lt;source&gt;</code></a> element: the browser will choose the most suitable one. It can also be the destination for streamed media, using a <a title=\"The MediaStream interface represents a stream of media content. A stream consists of several tracks such as video or audio tracks. Each track is specified as an instance of MediaStreamTrack.\" href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaStream\"><code>MediaStream</code></a>.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;img&gt; element represents an image in the document.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/img.html\"><code>&lt;img&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> element</strong> represents an image in the document.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;map&gt; element is used with &lt;area&gt; elements to define an image map (a clickable link area).\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/map.html\"><code>&lt;map&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;map&gt;</code> element</strong> is used with <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;area&gt; element defines a hot-spot region on an image, and optionally associates it with a hypertext link. This element is used only within a &lt;map&gt; element.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/area.html\"><code>&lt;area&gt;</code></a> elements to define an image map (a clickable link area).</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;track&gt; element is used as a child of the media elements &lt;audio&gt; and &lt;video&gt;. It lets you specify timed text tracks (or time-based data), for example to automatically handle subtitles. The tracks are formatted in WebVTT format (.vtt files) — Web Video Text Tracks.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/track.html\"><code>&lt;track&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;track&gt;</code> element</strong> is used as a child of the media elements <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;audio&gt; element is used to embed sound content in documents. It may contain one or more audio sources, represented using the src attribute or the &lt;source&gt; element: the browser will choose the most suitable one. It can also be the destination for streamed media, 