(164, 1, '2018-10-16 13:35:55', '2018-10-16 10:35:55', 'In addition to regular multimedia content, HTML can include a variety of other content, even if it\'s not always easy to interact with.\r\n<table class=\"standard-table\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Element</th>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;embed&gt; element represents an integration point for an external application or interactive content (in other words, a plug-in).\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/embed.html\"><code>&lt;embed&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;embed&gt;</code> element</strong> represents an integration point for an external application or interactive content (in other words, a plug-in).</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;object&gt; element represents an external resource, which can be treated as an image, a nested browsing context, or a resource to be handled by a plugin.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/object.html\"><code>&lt;object&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;object&gt;</code> element</strong> represents an external resource, which can be treated as an image, a nested browsing context, or a resource to be handled by a plugin.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;param&gt; element defines parameters for an &lt;object&gt; element.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/param.html\"><code>&lt;param&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;param&gt;</code> element</strong> defines parameters for an <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;object&gt; element represents an external resource, which can be treated as an image, a nested browsing context, or a resource to be handled by a plugin.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/object.html\"><code>&lt;object&gt;</code></a> element.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;source&gt; element specifies multiple media resources for either the &lt;picture&gt;, the &lt;audio&gt; or the &lt;video&gt; element. It is an empty element. It is commonly used to serve the same media content in multiple formats supported by different browsers.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/source.html\"><code>&lt;source&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;source&gt;</code> element</strong> specifies multiple media resources for either the <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;picture&gt; element is a container used to specify multiple &lt;source&gt; elements for a specific &lt;img&gt; contained in it. The browser will choose the most suitable source according to the current layout of the page (the constraints of the box the image will appear in) and the device it will be displayed on (e.g. a normal or hiDPI device.)\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/picture.html\"><code>&lt;picture&gt;</code></a>, the <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;audio&gt; element is used to embed sound content in documents. It may contain one or more audio sources, represented using the src attribute or the &lt;source&gt; element: the browser will choose the most suitable one. It can also be the destination for streamed media, using a MediaStream.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/audio.html\"><code>&lt;audio&gt;</code></a> or the <a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Use the HTML &lt;video&gt; element to embed video content in a document.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/video.html\"><code>&lt;video&gt;</code></a> element. It is an empty element. It is commonly used to serve the same media content in <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Media_formats_supported_by_the_audio_and_video_elements\">multiple formats supported by different browsers</a>.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Embedded content', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'embedded-content', '', '', '2018-10-16 13:36:43', '2018-10-16 10:36:43', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=164', 0, 'post', '', 0),
