(168, 1, '2018-10-16 13:36:14', '2018-10-16 10:36:14', 'In order to create dynamic content and Web applications, HTML supports the use of scripting languages, most prominently JavaScript. Certain elements support this capability.\r\n<table class=\"standard-table\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Element</th>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"Use the HTML &lt;canvas&gt; element with the canvas scripting API to draw graphics and animations.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/canvas.html\"><code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>Use the <strong>HTML <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code> element</strong> with the <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API\">canvas scripting API </a>to draw graphics and animations.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;noscript&gt; element defines a section of HTML to be inserted if a script type on the page is unsupported or if scripting is currently turned off in the browser.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/noscript.html\"><code>&lt;noscript&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;noscript&gt;</code> element</strong> defines a section of HTML to be inserted if a script type on the page is unsupported or if scripting is currently turned off in the browser.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; color: #387894; text-decoration: none;\" title=\"The HTML &lt;script&gt; element is used to embed or reference an executable script.\" href=\"http://docset.velocity/HTML.docset/developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/script.html\"><code>&lt;script&gt;</code></a></td>\r\n<td>The <stron